    "system": {
        "description": {
            "value": "<p><em>You sprinkle a bit of lapis lazuli dust over an area, visualizing a scene within your mind, deftly twisting a piece of fleece to match the general shape of your illusion as you give it verbal instructions.</em></p><p><strong>Materials:</strong> You require 0.2 pounds of pure @UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-spells.Item.obmHkoF0Lp9AX6P8]{Lapis Lazuli Dust}, typically valued at 20 gold. This spell consumes this material.</p><p dir=\"auto\" id=\"viewer-nmest4883\"><strong>Illusory Image</strong> </p><p>Roll an &amp;Reference[illusoryimages]{illusion check} for this spell. If you roll less than 10 on the D20, count the roll as a 10.</p><ul><li aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"auto\"><p id=\"viewer-1nbdk4884\">You create an illusion of an object, a creature, or some other visible phenomenon that is no larger than a 30-foot cube. You can also create illusory sounds, smells, and temperature, and your illusion can be in motion. Your illusion cannot create an extreme temperature, loud sound, or otherwise extreme effect that would damage or otherwise harm a creature.</p></li><li aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"auto\"><p>You create an illusion that can go on for up to 10 minutes before resetting. Your illusion can move to other locations within 120 ft. of your original casting location. Choose one of the following three options:</p><ul><li aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"auto\"><p><strong>Triggered Illusion:</strong> Set a condition for your illusion to activate. You can create an illusion with a set routine that lasts up to 10 minutes in length. If your conditions are met, the illusion activates. Once activated, it cannot activate again until it is finished.</p></li><li aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"auto\"><p><strong>Looping Illusion:</strong> Your illusion plays constantly, resetting to the beginning when it is finished its loop, which can be up to 10 minutes long.</p></li><li aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"auto\"><p><strong>Complex Illusion:</strong> By casting this spell again in the same place, you can lengthen an illusion by up to 10 minutes, or create a conditional branch on your illusion. For example, if you had a Looping Illusion of a scarecrow, you could use a Complex Illusion to make the scarecrow shriek when someone comes close, then return to its usual loop.</p></li></ul></li></ul><p></p><p><em>Unlike most permanent spells, this spell can be dispelled.</em></p>",
            "chat": "<strong>Materials:</strong> You require 0.2 pounds of pure @UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-spells.Item.obmHkoF0Lp9AX6P8]{Lapis Lazuli Dust}, typically valued at 20 gold. This spell consumes this material.</p><p dir=\"auto\" id=\"viewer-nmest4883\"><strong>Illusory Image</strong> </p><p>Roll an &amp;Reference[illusoryimages]{illusion check} for this spell. If you roll less than 10 on the D20, count the roll as a 10.</p><ul><li aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"auto\"><p id=\"viewer-1nbdk4884\">You create an illusion of an object, a creature, or some other visible phenomenon that is no larger than a 30-foot cube. You can also create illusory sounds, smells, and temperature, and your illusion can be in motion. Your illusion cannot create an extreme temperature, loud sound, or otherwise extreme effect that would damage or otherwise harm a creature.</p></li><li aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"auto\"><p>You create an illusion that can go on for up to 10 minutes before resetting. Your illusion can move to other locations within 120 ft. of your original casting location. Choose one of the following three options:</p><ul><li aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"auto\"><p><strong>Triggered Illusion:</strong> Set a condition for your illusion to activate. You can create an illusion with a set routine that lasts up to 10 minutes in length. If your conditions are met, the illusion activates. Once activated, it cannot activate again until it is finished.</p></li><li aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"auto\"><p><strong>Looping Illusion:</strong> Your illusion plays constantly, resetting to the beginning when it is finished its loop, which can be up to 10 minutes long.</p></li><li aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"auto\"><p><strong>Complex Illusion:</strong> By casting this spell again in the same place, you can lengthen an illusion by up to 10 minutes, or create a conditional branch on your illusion. For example, if you had a Looping Illusion of a scarecrow, you could use a Complex Illusion to make the scarecrow shriek when someone comes close, then return to its usual loop.</p></li></ul></li></ul><p></p>"
        },
